<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1188758-just-a-timeline-question-the">Just a timeline question. The &quot;translation&quot; at the beginning of the book says the manuscript was dated 500 CE, but St Brigid of Kildare lived until 530s. How was Gwynneve praying to a dead St Brigid if Brigid lived past the year 500 CE? Very confused. Can anyone explain?</a>
</div>
