              <span id="reviewTextContainer14401834" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5348585319147809366"><b>Beautifully written</b>, every line is like poetry. It&apos;s romantic without being cheesy and mourns for the lost celtic culture. The relationship between the main character and her love is portrayed tenderly and innocently, just like ones first love can be.I think this is the kind of story we don&apos;t hear about...the casualties of when one culture invades another.<br/><br/>Words can not express how much I love this novel, the beauty of it astonished me. I simply could NOT put it down.</span>
  <span id="freeText5348585319147809366" style="display:none"><b>Beautifully written</b>, every line is like poetry. It's romantic without being cheesy and mourns for the lost celtic culture. The relationship between the main character and her love is portrayed tenderly and innocently, just like ones first love can be.I think this is the kind of story we don't hear about...the casualties of when one culture invades another.<br /><br />Words can not express how much I love this novel, the beauty of it astonished me. I simply could NOT put it down.</span>
