  <span id="freeText9960239851109434538" style="display:none">I started this book with little expectation and the story story ended up being quite captivating. The beginning was some what boring but afterwards it was a real page-turner. The protagonist is Gwynneve tells the story of her life, a woman raised pagan,trained as a druid and "converted" to a Christianity. <br /><br />The underlying theme deals with questions about the meaning and origin of faith as Gwynneve struggles to understand the two dominant belief systems of her lifetime. The end of the story is so moving. I was outraged and saddened. A book worth reading. Loved the use of language:clear and humble.<br /></span>
