<span id="freeTextContainer14029691700905866321">Beautifully written but heartbreaking tale that illustrates how the evils of human nature, disguised as organized religion, seeks to obliterate the spiritual aspects of the natural world in favor of their invisible tyrant in the sky. My heart broke for Gwynn and even for Giannon. Gwynn, a pagan Druid living as a Catholic nun in Ireland, is caught up in a whirlwind of disaster, the outcome of which we pagans know all too well. This book touched my heart. Even though it is fiction, it was based on</span>
  <span id="freeText14029691700905866321" style="display:none">Beautifully written but heartbreaking tale that illustrates how the evils of human nature, disguised as organized religion, seeks to obliterate the spiritual aspects of the natural world in favor of their invisible tyrant in the sky. My heart broke for Gwynn and even for Giannon. Gwynn, a pagan Druid living as a Catholic nun in Ireland, is caught up in a whirlwind of disaster, the outcome of which we pagans know all too well. This book touched my heart. Even though it is fiction, it was based on the author’s research and reads like non-fiction. Warning: it will break your heart. </span>
